Facial Landmark Detection with Dlib¶

In this lesson we'll learn:¶

  1. Apply Facial Landmark Detection

Facial landmarks are used to localize and represent salient regions of the face, such as:

Eyes

  • Eyebrows
  • Nose
  • Mouth
  • jawline Facial landmarks have been successfully applied to face alignment, head pose estimation, face swapping, blink detection and much more.

For more information: (https://pyimagesearch.com/2017/04/03/facial-landmarks-dlib-opencv-python/)

Shunday qilib, yuz belgilarini aniqlash ikki bosqichli jarayondir:

1-qadam: Rasmdagi yuzni lokalizatsiya qiling. 2-qadam: Yuz ROIdagi asosiy yuz tuzilmalarini aniqlang.

Understanding dlibs facial landmark detector

The pre-trained facial landmark detector inside the dlib library is used to estimate the location of 68 (x, y)-coordinates that map to facial structures on the face.

The indexes of the 68 coordinates can be visualized on the image below:

# Our Setup, Import Libaries, Create our Imshow Function and Download our Images
import cv2
import dlib
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

# Define our imshow function 
def imshow(title = "Image", image = None, size = 10):
    w, h = image.shape[0], image.shape[1]
    aspect_ratio = w/h
    plt.figure(figsize=(size * aspect_ratio,size))
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

#from imutils import face_utils da mavjud funksiya 

#for convinience uchun, dlib face_detectordan kelgan
#rectangle qiymatlarni bbox coordinatesga ga ogirib olyapmiz. 
def rect_to_bb(rect): 
  # take a bounding predicted by dlib and convert it
	# to the format (x, y, w, h) as we would normally do with OpenCV
  x = rect.left()
  y = rect.top()
  w = rect.right() - x 
  h = rect.bottom() - y 

  #return coordinates as tuple
  return (x, y, w, h)
In [73]:
#from imutils import face_utils da mavjud funksiya 
def shape_to_np(shape, dtype="int"):
  """ Face landmark detectordan qaytgan object coordinatesni np.arrayga 
  o'tkazib olyapmiz shtobi play nicer in future works"""

  # initialize the list of (x, y)-coordinates 
  #chunki dlib face landmark detector 68 ta x,y coordinatalarni objectini qaytaradi 
  coords = np.zeros(shape=(68,2))  

  #loop over 68 facial landmarks and convert 
  #them to a 2-tuple of (x,y) coordinates
  for i in range(0,68):
    coords[i] = (shape.part(i).x, shape.part(i).y)

  return coords

#loop over face detection 
for i, rect in enumerate(rectangles):
  #facial landmark ni  olish uchun dlib shape predictor classiga rasm va face roi ni yuboramiz
  shape = predictor(gray, rect) 
  # shape bu facial landmark (x, y)-coordinates object bolgani uchun
  #uni np.arrayga o'tkazib olamiz
  np_shape = face_utils.shape_to_np(shape)
  print(np_shape.shape) #68,2 matrix qaytaradi. yani 68 ta facial landmark nuqtalar

  #dlib rect formatdagi rectangle qiymatlarni OPENCV style ga o'tkazamiz
  #in order to draw rectangle
  (x, y, w, h) = face_utils.rect_to_bb(rect) 
  cv2.rectangle(image, (x,y), (x+w, h+y), (0,255,0),2)

  #show the number of faces in Text
  cv2.putText(image, f"Face N #{i+1}", (x-10, y-10),
              cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 1, (0, 255, 0), 2)
  
  #loop over np_shape facial landmark points and draw circle 
  i=1
  for (x, y) in np_shape:
     cv2.putText(image, f"{i}", (x, y), cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.5, (0, 0, 255), 1)
     #cv2.circle(image, (x, y), 2, (0, 0, 255), 2)
     i+=1
imshow('result', image)

2. Facial Landmark Detection Modern computer vision version¶

In [79]:
PREDICTOR_PATH = "shape_predictor_68_face_landmarks.dat"
landmark_predictor = dlib.shape_predictor(PREDICTOR_PATH)
face_detector = dlib.get_frontal_face_detector() #face detection uchun. 

class TooManyFaces(Exception):
    pass

class NoFaces(Exception):
    pass

def get_landmarks(im):
    rects = face_detector(im, 1)

    #1 dan koproq yuz topsa TooManyFaces classi ishga tushadi
    if len(rects) > 1: 
        raise TooManyFaces 
    #Agar topa olmasa, NoFaces klassi ishga tushadi 
    if len(rects) == 0:
        raise NoFaces

    # facial landmark x va y pointlarni np.matrix sifatida qaytaradi. 
    return np.matrix([[p.x, p.y] for p in predictor(im, rects[0]).parts()])

def annotate_landmarks(im, landmarks):
    im = im.copy()
    for idx, point in enumerate(landmarks):
        pos = (point[0, 0], point[0, 1]) # x va y coordinatalarni olish
        cv2.putText(im, str(idx), pos,
                    fontFace=cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SCRIPT_SIMPLEX,
                    fontScale=0.4,
                    
                    color=(0, 0, 255))
        cv2.circle(im, pos, 3, color=(0, 255, 255))
    return im

image = cv2.imread('images/Trump.jpg')
imshow('Original', image)
landmarks = get_landmarks(image)
image_with_landmarks = annotate_landmarks(image, landmarks)
imshow('Result', image_with_landmarks)
